							<p class="mb-8 text-md text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-justify md:text-left" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="100">
								A platform made for the purpose of recruitment.
								As a <span class="text-gray-100">lead for this project</span>, I collaborated with and  <span class="text-gray-100">mentored a team of 5 interns</span>.
								This website was made during my tenure as a full-stack engineer at <a class="text-secondary-500 hover:text-primary-500" href="https://kansastek.us/">HiringTek</a> (sister company of KansasTek). <br><br>
								I developed this application  <span class="text-gray-100">handling all aspects of development</span>, from the  <span class="text-gray-100">front-end</span> to the  <span class="text-gray-100">back-end</span> and also for  <span class="text-gray-100">deployment</span> and  <span class="text-gray-100">maintenance</span>.
								The front-end used  <span class="text-gray-100">JavaScript</span>,  <span class="text-gray-100">TypeScript</span>, and  <span class="text-gray-100">Angular</span>, whereas the back-end was developed with  <span class="text-gray-100">Node.js</span> for the server, and  <span class="text-gray-100">Express.js</span> for REST APIs.
								The website was hosted on  <span class="text-gray-100">Google Cloud Platform</span> with load balancing, deployed using  <span class="text-gray-100">Kubernetes</span> and  <span class="text-gray-100">Docker</span>.
								This project also helped me learn  <span class="text-gray-100">DevOps</span> using  <span class="text-gray-100">Jenkins CI/CD pipeline</span> for automated deployment to GCP. <br><br>
								The jobs displayed in the image were only for development purposes. This application is no longer active.
							</p>

